# WebDetection

Detectors match page conditions (text patterns, element selectors) and fire events or collect breakage report data.

## Detector naming

Detector and group names must match `[a-zA-Z0-9][a-zA-Z0-9_]*`.

## fireEvent.type constraint

Every `fireEvent.type` value must correspond to a `source` in an eventHub telemetry parameter. This is enforced by tests — adding a detector with a new `fireEvent.type` without a matching eventHub entry will fail validation.

## Schema

Detectors are defined in `settings.detectors` as nested groups:

```json
"detectors": {
    "groupName": {
        "detectorName": {
            "state": "enabled",
            "match": { "text": { "pattern": "...", "selector": "..." } },
            "actions": { "fireEvent": { "type": "eventType" } }
        }
    }
}
```
